![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/a8b40ae9-fd37-4241-a908-7c20a157b43d/20240525_102531.jpg?format=original)

According to Fightful, Becky Lynch's WWE contract is set to expire on June 1st, and negotiations for a new deal are ongoing. If an agreement isn't reached by the end of this week, Lynch will officially become a free agent, leaving her future with the company uncertain.

Lynch, a cornerstone of the WWE women's division, has been a driving force behind the company's evolution. Her meteoric rise to fame, captivating persona, and impressive in-ring skills have made her a fan favorite and a vital asset to the WWE.

The possibility of Lynch becoming a free agent has sparked concern among fans and industry insiders alike. Her departure would be a significant blow to the WWE, as she has played a crucial role in shaping the women's division and inspiring a new generation of female wrestlers.

The WWE will likely work diligently to secure a new deal with Lynch, considering her immense value to the company. However, if negotiations fail, Lynch may explore other opportunities, potentially shaking up the professional wrestling landscape.

As the deadline looms, fans eagerly await news of Lynch's contract status. Will she remain a key figure in the WWE, or will she embark on a new chapter in her career? Only time will tell. One thing is certain, though – Becky Lynch's impact on the world of professional wrestling will be felt for years to come.